!!!
%html{:lang => "en"}
  %head
    %meta{:charset => "utf-8"}
    %meta{:content => "IE=edge", "http-equiv" => "X-UA-Compatible"}
    %meta{:content => "width=device-width, initial-scale=1", :name => "viewport"}
    %meta{:content => "", :name => "description"}
    %meta{:content => "", :name => "author"}
    / Custom Fonts
    %link{:href => "http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400,700,300italic,400italic,700italic", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}
    / HTML5 Shim and Respond.js IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries
    / WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file://
    /[if lt IE 9]
      <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/libs/html5shiv/3.7.0/html5shiv.js"></script>
      <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/libs/respond.js/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
  %body
    / Header
    .intro-header
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            .intro-message
              %h1 Create one awesome badge
              %h1 for your event
              %h3 And print it a lot of times using the list of your participants in 3 steps
              %hr.intro-divider
                %ul.list-inline.intro-social-buttons
                  %li
                    %a.btn.btn-default.btn-lg{:href => "#"}
                      %i.fa.fa-fw
                      %span.network-name How it work?
      / /.container
    / /.intro-header
    / Page Content
    .content-section-a
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-5.col-sm-6
            %hr.section-heading-spacer
              .clearfix
              %h2.section-heading
                Upload the mockup of badge
                <br>in SVG format
              %p.lead
                After that upload the list of your participants in csv format.
                We will support other formats of input files in the nearest future.
          .col-lg-5.col-lg-offset-2.col-sm-6
            %img.img-responsive{:alt => "", :src => "assets/ipad.png"}
      / /.container
    / /.content-section-a
    .content-section-b
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-5.col-lg-offset-1.col-sm-push-6.col-sm-6
            %hr.section-heading-spacer
              .clearfix
              %h2.section-heading
                Check the fields that must
                %br be at the badge
              %p.lead
                and press the button 'Generate'. Wait some time for processing your csv-file and generating a single images.
                We take the fields about your participants and put them to single images automatically.
          .col-lg-5.col-sm-pull-6.col-sm-6
            %img.img-responsive{:alt => "", :src => "assets/dog.png"}
      / /.container
    / /.content-section-b
    .content-section-a
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-5.col-sm-6
            %hr.section-heading-spacer
              .clearfix
              %h2.section-heading
                Yay! Now you can download your badges in a zip-archive.
              %p.lead
          .col-lg-5.col-lg-offset-2.col-sm-6
            %img.img-responsive{:alt => "", :src => "assets/phones.png"}
      / /.container
    / /.content-section-a
    .banner
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-6
            %h2 Let's get started!
          .col-lg-6
            %ul.list-inline.banner-social-buttons
              %li
                %a.btn.btn-default.btn-lg{:href => "/load"}
                  %i.fa.fa-twitter.fa-fw
                  %span.network-name Go to make badges
      / /.container
    / /.banner
    / Footer
    %footer
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            %ul.list-inline
              %li
                %a{:href => "#"} Home
            %p.copyright.text-muted.small Was made at RailsRumble 2014.
